    - 'Li Yan-nian: A Han Dynasty official under Emperor Wu, renowned for music and appointed Director of Music.'
    - 'Cai Yuanding: A Song Dynasty scholar who wrote the ''New Writings on Pitch and Temperament'' (Lülü Xinshū).'
    - 'The music of Xianchi and Shao: Xianchi represents the music of the Yellow Emperor; Shao represents the music of Sage-King Shun; mentioned here as exemplars of virtuous music.'
