    - 'The giant millet (jushi): A type of grain historically used as a unit of measurement for establishing pitch standards, with 100 millet seeds equaling one Chinese inch of the yellow bell pitch standard.'
    - 'The Two Altered Modes: Referring to the altered gong and altered seventh tone in traditional music theory.'
    - 'The Four Elevated Tones: Referring to the elevated versions of gong, shang, jiao, and zhi tones.'
